For the past year we silently dealt with the unexpected. Cancer crept into our family and created an entirely new reality. Day in and day out, we faced challenges we’ve never experienced, all 3 of us. 

However, it was a privilege to have spent your last year, months, and days with you, and you did things your way. These 10 months changed my perspective and this past week has changed my heart. Always for the better. 

You did good, and we’re about to live it up for you! This isn’t goodbye, but see you later 🤍
I love you forever girl and we’re gonna miss you like crazy 🤍🕊️

“I Know That It’s God Up There Giving Me The Signs” 

Darian told me this was main feed material 😂🫶🏾 @darian 

For me, this post has more to do with my excitement for my future than anything. Lately I have been feeling so optimistic and little things like this really make my visions for myself a liiiiiitle clearer. 

I am always equally shocked when people find out the “Girl Don’t Do It” sound is mine, but this was all love. 

From this moment and all the moments in between, it helps me understand that alllll of these moments (big or small) are impactful in different ways to the grand picture and it’s our job to embrace these things as they come. To me, the sound was so small, but seeing how people react helps me see it differently. You never know what your journey looks like but it’s yours, and it’s designed for you. 🤍
